From 57220b54f7f9749112da635659707d274825d1cc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kenneth Kasilag <kenneth@kasilag.me>
Date: Wed, 11 Mar 2026 11:37:34 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] uboot-airoha: add chainloader support for Gemtek XR1710G

Similar to the Gemtek W1700K, issues regarding BMT/BBT support
and the risk of unwanted remapping necessitate the use of a
chainloader to boot the OS from a UBI volume; separating all
writes between the BMT/BBT-aware vendor bootloader and Linux,
which manages any remapping needed in the UBI layer.

Signed-off-by: Kenneth Kasilag <kenneth@kasilag.me>
---
 configs/an7581_xr1710g_defconfig                     | 107 ++++++++++
 defenvs/an7581_xr1710g_env                           |  27 +++
 dts/upstream/src/arm64/airoha/an7581-xr1710g-ubi.dts | 131 +++++++++++
 3 files changed, 265 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 configs/an7581_xr1710g_defconfig
 create mode 100644 defenvs/an7581_xr1710g_env
 create mode 100644 dts/upstream/src/arm64/airoha/an7581-xr1710g-ubi.dts

diff --git a/configs/an7581_xr1710g_defconfig b/configs/an7581_xr1710g_defconfig
new file mode 100644
index 1230e879da2664..ad3b2bf9ecbf03 100644
